# Resume Parser — Technical Architecture & Stack Documentation

> **Version:** 1.0.0 | **Author:** Praktiki Team | **Last Updated:** March 2, 2026  
> *This document covers the complete technology stack, system architecture, data flow, and module-level design of the Praktiki Resume Parser — ready for inclusion in a PRD.*

---

## 1. System Overview

The Praktiki Resume Parser is a **production-grade, AI-powered microservice** that automatically extracts structured data from PDF resumes. It transforms unstructured resume documents into a standardized JSON schema containing the candidate's name, email, phone number, technical skills, and work experience.

### Key Capabilities
- Accepts PDF uploads via REST API
- Extracts 5 core fields: **Name, Email, Phone, Skills, Experience**
- Uses a **hybrid NLP pipeline** combining rule-based extraction, NER (Named Entity Recognition), and semantic similarity
- Supports batch processing (up to 10 resumes/batch)
- Includes built-in production monitoring, human feedback loop, and accuracy tracking
- Avg processing time: ~2 seconds per resume

