## 8. Accuracy & Performance Benchmarks

### Tested on 120 IT Resumes (INFORMATION-TECHNOLOGY dataset)

| Field | Extraction Rate | Format Quality |
|-------|----------------|----------------|
| Skills | 100.0% | 100.0% |
| Experience | 14.2% | — |
| Phone | 12.5% | 86.7% |
| Name | 8.3% | 70.0% |
| Email | 0.8% | 100.0% |

> [!NOTE]
> Low entity extraction rates on this dataset are due to anonymized/redacted contact information and non-standard date formats in the test resumes. The parser performs significantly better on standard resumes with visible contact details.

### Performance

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Avg processing time | ~2 seconds/resume |
| PDF text extraction | 100% success rate |
| Max batch size | 10 resumes |
| Model startup time | ~13 seconds |

