## 10. Security Considerations

| Area | Implementation |
|------|---------------|
| **File validation** | Extension whitelist (.pdf only), file size limits (10MB) |
| **CORS** | Restricted to specific origins (EC2 IP + localhost) |
| **Input sanitization** | Pydantic validation on all request/response models |
| **Error handling** | Graceful error responses, no stack traces in production |
| **Logging** | Structured JSONL logging, sensitive data excluded |

---

## 11. Summary for PRD

The Praktiki Resume Parser is an **AI-powered microservice** built on **FastAPI** that uses a **hybrid NLP pipeline** to extract structured data from PDF resumes. It combines:

- **RoBERTa-based NER** (spaCy `en_core_web_trf`) for contact info extraction
- **4-stage skill extraction** using exact matching, alias resolution, fuzzy matching (difflib), and **FAISS-powered semantic search** with Sentence-Transformer embeddings
- **Rule-based experience extraction** using regex date patterns and contextual analysis

The system is deployed as a standalone service on AWS EC2 (port 8001), processes resumes in ~2 seconds, includes built-in production monitoring with human feedback loops, and exposes a fully documented REST API with Swagger/ReDoc auto-generated documentation.
